The paper proposes a new algorithm for image and video compression using a pruned approximate eight-point discrete cosine transform (DCT) that requires only ten additions. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) category, which deals with the study of information processing, transmission, and storage. Additionally, the paper involves digital synthesis in CMOS technology, which could also place it in the Multimedia (cs.MM) category, which deals with the processing and analysis of multimedia data. The paper also mentions image and video compression, which could place it in the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Augmented Reality (cs.AR) categories, respectively. Finally, the paper could also belong to the Electromagnetics (cs.EM) category, which deals with the study of electromagnetic fields and their interactions with matter, as the proposed algorithm involves digital synthesis in CMOS technology.
